name: CKEditor Bootstrap Tabs
tagline: A plugin for CKEditor that allows for the user to insert and edit a specified number of Bootstrap tabs.
body:
## Installation
1. Download the zip file.
- Extract the contents to your CKEditor plugins directory: `/path/to/ckeditor/plugins/bootstrapTabs`.
- Note: The name of the folder must be `bootstrapTabs`, not `ckeditor-bootstrap-tabs`.
note: Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration.
